    "CONTENT": {
        "Career": "Gregersen spent his early career playing in both the Faroe Islands and Denmark, for Randers FC, Lyngby BK, GÍ Gøta, IF Skjold, BK Frem and Víkingur. He signed for Scottish club Ross County in June 2010, before leaving the club in February 2011, having made just one appearance for them in the League Cup.Gregersen made his international debut in 2009, and by 2010 he was national team captain.Scores and results list the Faroe Islands' goal tally first.",
